    dc:date "2006" ;
    dc:title "Gollumjapyx smeagol gen. n., sp. n., an enigmatic hypogean japygid (Diplura: Japygidae) from the eastern Iberian Peninsula" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.174944>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.174945>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.174947>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.174946>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.174948>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.174949> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.174944>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Habitus of Gollumjapyx smeagol Sendra & Ortuño sp. n. (scale: 3 mm)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/174944/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.174945>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. a. Gollumjapyx smeagol Sendra & Ortuño sp. n., Avenc d’en Serenge cave from Cabanes, Castellón (Spain); b. detail of the contents from the digestive tract belonging to a specimen from Avenc d’en Serenge; all the fragments belong to a male of Speleotyphlus aurouxi (Carabidae, Anillini). Terms: a, antennomeres; rgs, ring of the genital segment; ml, median lobe; p, paramere; t, tarsomeres. (scales, a: 3 mm, b: 0.3 mm)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/174945/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.174947>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Gollumjapyx smeagol Sendra & Ortuño sp. n.. a. Vertex, young specimen from Avenc Mas Nou; b. Vertex, holotype; c. Pronotum, holotype; d. Mesonotum, holotype; e. Metanotum, holotype. Terms: A, S, V, M, I, P groups of large setae in vertex; M, macrochaeta thoracic. (scales: 1 mm)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/174947/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.174946>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Scanning electron microscope photography of Gollumjapyx smeagol Sendra & Ortuño sp. n.. a. apical antennomere; b. XXXV antennomere; c. urite X and cerci, dorsal view; d. urite X and cerci, ventral view. Terms: p, placoid sensilla; ss, short sensilla. (scales, a and b: 25 µm; c and d: 500 µm)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/174946/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.174948>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Gollumjapyx smeagol Sendra & Ortuño sp. n., holotype. a. Tergites V to IX; b. Urite X and cerci, dorsal view. Term: M, macrochaeta; m, microchaeta; ls, large setae. (scale: 1 mm)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/174948/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.174949>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Gollumjapyx smeagol Sendra & Ortuño sp. n., paratype female from Avenc Canals pit. a. urosternite I; b. Details of sensory and glandular setae of lateral subcoxal organ. Terms: st, styli; GS, glandular setae; SS, sensory setae. (scales, a: 0.5 mm; b: 0.05 mm)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/174949/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

